extended: The area designated is a rough triangular bounded by Broadway and Wall, Pearl and Whitehall Streets. A number of streets in the area, such as Beaver, Bridge, Marketfield and Wall, carry English translations of their original Dutch names. Broadway, the oldest path in the city, was originally an Indian trail whose Algonquin name was Wickquasgeck, which means birch-bark country.
